The ultimate showdown! Luigi’s Mansion vs Dark Moon! Which game was better? I have only a month away until this series officially becomes a trilogy! I have played both games commendably and which game wins for me? The first original game hands down takes it! Dark Moon was amusing and had fun moments to play but I was never a fan of the mission modes. They were tacky, forgettable and the cartoony art style of both the ghosts and the design of the mansion (sorry more than 1 mansion I don’t know why they didn’t call it mansion(s) instead of singular) were a little run-of-the-mill here. I liked the affiliation of botany in the game but nothing more than that. The missions were bad and repetitive. But the original. Man.. the first game was not just the highest-selling GameCube game at that time. But LM1 was and still is my all-time favorite Nintendo game! BOTH The dark aesthetics in the game and the main theme song is what made this game legendary. You get to discover a full mansion in a one fully-throttled stage on your own instead of doing lousy missions. each and every portrait ghost has their own boss-like fight and each had a very distinctive story-telling in the room you catch them in. It felt more organic than Dark Moon’s mind-numbingly spontaneous levels where it doesn’t even feel like it’s all from one game. The design of the gameplay in the first one was more friendly, the architectural roofs, the music, the trademarking foyer, the hidden easter eggs and treasures. The secret rooms and the exploration each floor made it like a TRUE playfully spooky Halloween experience. Everything in this game was eerily indescribable compared to Dark Moon where I swear at some point during the game I felt like I was fucking playing Ghostbusters.

The announcement of Luigi’s Mansion 3 was the SOLE main reason why I’ve gotten myself a Switch in the first place. JUST like the time I got a PS4 back in 2013 EXCLUSIVELY for KH3’s announcement in that same year. 
I genuinely hope Nintendo doesn’t disappoint me with this one and I hope the 3rd game gets to live up to the first one’s expectations 👻🚪🔦💚 Which was your favorite and elaborate why? And are you excited for LM3!

🏃‍♂️💨

caption.text:
Except for a few more posters on the walls, @retro_gamer_mom and I finally got the guest room / game room finished!!! It felt so good to get so much of it out of boxes. Because we’ve decided to keep all gaming items (except consoles) in this rooms, we’ve had to put a few boxes of stuff in storage, but it was a lot of fun sorting through it all. @retro_gamer_son is so happy that he can come over and look through all of his Pokémon cards folders again!! Hope you enjoy the pics of the new set up!!
🕹🙋‍♂️
.
.

For this year’s Wrestling Club after school, I thought we should finally compete for real championship belts in our 2K video game tournaments instead of the cheap, foam toy ones. As a result, my classroom is now adorned with these two beautiful replica titles!

The WWE Intercontinental and World Heavyweight Championships are exact-scale replicas molded from the actual title belts used on television. Featuring stainless steel plates and weighing over 5 lbs. each, these straps are already a huge hit with my students, who can’t wait to get their hands on the gold! 💯

caption.text:
Don't mind me and my mini reobsession with Naruto 😶 it's only been nearly a decade since I worked on some of these characters :0 here's been my progression with Zabuza and Kakashi. I didn't realize at all that I basically made them in reflected poses to one another. Almost like they were destined to fight 🤔
The ones from 2008 were Pokémon Sprite edits. It wasn't until late 2009 and then 2010 that I go into doing them from scratch. Apparently my anatomy was way off back then 😂

caption.text: I don’t know what happened.

SURPRESAAA!!!!!
Estamos grávidos 😭
Gente vocês não têm ideia da nossa felicidade! Muitos não sabem mas eu tenho uma grande dificuldade pra engravidar devido à um problema em meu útero(síndrome dos ovários policísticos ) E estávamos tentando a 2 anos, tivemos 3 abortos durante essa fase. Foi muito difícil para mim e para meu marido mas no final nos planos de Deus tudo da certo no tempo dEle. 
Temos um bebê arco-iris 🌈
Obviamente é uma gravidez de risco mas estou sendo acompanhada pela minha médica maravilhosa a Dr. Heloyse. 
Estou de 17 semanas ( mais ou menos 4 meses) mas eu ainda não vi o sexo do bebê 😬😂. Ansiedade a mil!!!
Como podem perceber minha barriga é pequena demaiss haha  A Aurora amou a notícia e está super animada com a chegada da irmazinha(o) 
eu to torcendo demais para virem gêmeos já que temos uma grande probabilidade segundo a minha médica.

I finished Link's Awakening earlier on today (I dunno about you but you have to 100% everything before you can tackle the final boss, right?!)
Just wanted to give my thoughts!

This is absolutely how a remake should be handled. I loved it from start the finish. I remember the art style throwing a few people when it was originally unveiled but I thought it was cute as hell then and thanks to the sound it makes when you dash with the Pegasus Boots I think it's even more cute now 😍 The soundtrack matches the chibi-esque style perfectly.
However.
The was one new feature that downright annoyed me... Dampe's dungeon creator. For anyone else who went ahead and completed the Gold Challenges, I have one word. Stairs.
Good God. I'm not sure I can do this justice in text but you cannot (as far as I know) manually connect stairs to stairs. This made "Bows > Swords" really frustrating because the damn stairs just wouldn't connect to the ones I wanted them to connect with! It seems to connect stairwells to the ones closest so it's "easy" to work around but I shouldn't have to find a work around 😅 You could argue this was just an add on and has no real impact on the main game, and you'd be half right... some of the optional collectibles (heart/bottle/seashell) are locked behind Dampe's tutorials. You can also only use preexisting dungeon rooms... Which means you're replaying rooms from previous dungeons over and over again. With a little work and a bit more freedom I'm sure a Zelda Dungeon Creator would make a fantastic little eshop game but as it is now I'd give it little more that a "meh".
BUT I DID LOVE THE GAME, HONESTLY. DON'T READ TOO MUCH INTO MY BITCHING ABOUT FUCKING STAIRS 😂 
I probably should have started in Hero Mode because with the new addition of bottles the game was waaaaay easier.
------------------------------------------------
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

caption.text:
My only Retro World Expo pickups this year. I was alittle disappointed this year. Not in the expo itself, more in the exhibitors. Either they didnt have "expo" worthy games or the ones they did were waaaaaay overpriced. I had money burning a hole in my pocket and there was nothing worth it for me to buy. I was looking for some pricey games today but I wasnt overpaying. But other than that I had a good time. Lots of free games to play, panels to attend, youtubers to meet. Its run very smoothly and Ill be back everytime its around.

caption.text:
The ultimate showdown! Luigi’s Mansion vs Dark Moon! Which game was better? I have only a month away until this series officially becomes a trilogy! I have played both games commendably and which game wins for me? The first original game hands down takes it! Dark Moon was amusing and had fun moments to play but I was never a fan of the mission modes. They were tacky, forgettable and the cartoony art style of both the ghosts and the design of the mansion (sorry more than 1 mansion I don’t know why they didn’t call it mansion(s) instead of singular) were a little run-of-the-mill here. I liked the affiliation of botany in the game but nothing more than that. The missions were bad and repetitive. But the original. Man.. the first game was not just the highest-selling GameCube game at that time. But LM1 was and still is my all-time favorite Nintendo game! BOTH The dark aesthetics in the game and the main theme song is what made this game legendary. You get to discover a full mansion in a one fully-throttled stage on your own instead of doing lousy missions. each and every portrait ghost has their own boss-like fight and each had a very distinctive story-telling in the room you catch them in. It felt more organic than Dark Moon’s mind-numbingly spontaneous levels where it doesn’t even feel like it’s all from one game. The design of the gameplay in the first one was more friendly, the architectural roofs, the music, the trademarking foyer, the hidden easter eggs and treasures. The secret rooms and the exploration each floor made it like a TRUE playfully spooky Halloween experience. Everything in this game was eerily indescribable compared to Dark Moon where I swear at some point during the game I felt like I was fucking playing Ghostbusters.

The announcement of Luigi’s Mansion 3 was the SOLE main reason why I’ve gotten myself a Switch in the first place. JUST like the time I got a PS4 back in 2013 EXCLUSIVELY for KH3’s announcement in that same year. 
I genuinely hope Nintendo doesn’t disappoint me with this one and I hope the 3rd game gets to live up to the first one’s expectations 👻🚪🔦💚 Which was your favorite and elaborate why? And are you excited for LM3!

Mario Kart Tour registra 20 milhões de downloads em 24 horas
.
Mario Kart Tour, novo jogo da famosa série de corrida da Nintendo que está disponível de graça para dispositivos móveis, registrou 20 milhões de downloads em apenas 24 horas segundo um levantamento do Sensor Tower. O número leva em consideração tanto a App Store quanto a Play Store.
.
Mario Kart Tour é o jogo mobile da Nintendo com o maior número de downloads no lançamento.
.
Segundo o site, o desempenho é quase três vezes maior do que o de Super Mario Run, que registrou 7 milhões de downloads no lançamento em 2016. Ele também é 31 vezes maior do que o número de Dr. Mario World, o título anterior da companhia que contou com 660 mil downloads no mesmo intervalo.
.
Disponível para Android e iOS, Mario Kart Tour é primeiro jogo da franquia de corrida para dispositivos móveis.
.
Em adição, foi revelado que mais de um milhão de dólares já foi arrecadado com o aplicativo. O Gold Pass que garante acesso a personagens e karts é o produto mais popular entre os usuários, mas, devido ao seu período de teste de 13 dias, o dinheiro ainda não foi computado — e há chances de muitas compras serem canceladas antes da cobrança.
.
Fonte: Gamesindustry
.
